Phishing Kit Hosted on Legitimate Cloud and CDN Platforms Targeting Microsoft and Google Users.
The most widespread and dangerous phishing campaigns today are powered by Adversary-in-the-Middle (AiTM) kits, which help unfold phishing attacks where threat actors become a proxy between the victim and a legitimate service.

The top three most active phishing kits remain Tycoon2FA, a Phishing-as-a-Service platform designed to bypass multi-factor authentication; 
Sneaky2FA, an AiTM threat used in Business Email Compromise attacks; and EvilProxy, a reverse-proxy phishing kit often used for account takeover attacks aimed at high-ranking executives.
